Code description:
The pipeline follows the approach described in Revealing Neurocognitive and Behavioral Patterns by Unsupervised Manifold Learning from Dynamic Brain Data (Zhou et al.). 
EEG trials are averaged per condition-continuous group to produce clean ERP signals, which are then preprocessed using temporal autocorrelation smoothing (TimeCORR) and spatial grid mapping via Gromov-Wasserstein optimal transport (NeuroMap), converting each timepoint into a 6×6 image.
A convolutional neural network is trained unsupervised using a recursive KL divergence strategy across four stages, where each stage recomputes the target similarity matrix from progressively deeper layer activations.
The trained BCNE model is then used to embed all group-averaged ERP epochs into a 2D space, which is compared against standard time-agnostic methods (PCA, t-SNE, UMAP, PHATE) and T-PHATE using KNN accuracy, RSA, trustworthiness, and continuity metrics. 

Steps to run:
1. Include the simulated data file in the data folder.
   a. Data can be simulated in Julia using Unfoldsim package, refer DataSimulation_UnfoldSim.jl file.
   b. Replace the csv filename with your file in main.py.
For BCNE (non linear dimensionality reduction):
2. Run python main.py to train the model for condition-continuous groups.
3. Run python compare_methods.py for comparing the model with PCA, t-SNE, UMAP, PHATE, TPHATE.
 
